      • getAllUndefinedConstantsRecursively

        public java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> getAllUndefinedConstantsRecursively(ConstantList constantList,
                                                                              LabelList labelList,
                                                                              PropertiesFile propertiesFile)
        Get all undefined constants used (i.e. in ExpressionConstant objects) recursively and return as a list. Recursive descent means that we also find constants that are used within other constants, labels, properties. We only recurse into constants/labels/properties in the passed in lists. Any others discovered are ignored (and not descended into). ConstantList must be non-null so that we can determine which constants are undefined; LabelList and PropertiesFile passed in as null are ignored.

      • evaluatePartially

        public ASTElement evaluatePartially(Values constantValues,
                                    Values varValues)
                             throws PrismLangException
        Evaluate partially: replace some constants and variables with actual values. Constants/variables are specified as Values objects; either can be left null. Warning: Unlike evaluate(), evaluatePartially() methods modify (and return) the expression.
        Throws:
        PrismLangException

      • evaluatePartially

        public ASTElement evaluatePartially(State substate,
                                    int[] varMap)
                             throws PrismLangException
        Evaluate partially: replace some variables with actual values. Variables are specified as a State object, indexed over a subset of all variables, and a mapping from indices (over all variables) to this subset (-1 if not in subset). Warning: Unlike evaluate(), evaluatePartially() methods modify (and return) the expression.
        Throws:
        PrismLangException
